{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Convergence rollout tail: Phase-3 consumer swap + live shadow validation + capped live heal\n\n## Summary\nHigh-risk tail of the baseline convergence rollout (carved from soar-quill-flare / 7d23). This AGENT (with\nACLI access) performs the live validation directly, with GUARANTEED cleanup of test artifacts in both live Jira\nand the local store. `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml` runs `rebar reconcile --mode live` every ~20 min.\n\n## Already landed (7d23, on main)\n- Phase-1 baseline dual-write SHADOW (`baseline_shadow.py`) behind `reconciler.baseline_dual_write`, with per-pass\n  `baseline_shadow_check` logging + `baseline_shadow_divergence` alert.\n- Circuit breaker (`check_blast_radius`, default 0.10) before the first acting mutation.\n\n## Key facts established (code-verified — the plan is built on these)\n- **The swap is namespace-COMPATIBLE.** In `_diff_fields`, `field_name` iterates `local_mapped` (output of\n  `_map_local_to_jira_fields`), which emits **JIRA** names (`\"summary\"`, `outbound_fields.py:138,371-378`).\n  `prev_snapshot[jira_key]` is JIRA-keyed (`_snapshot_schema.py:135`), and `BindingStore.get_baseline` returns the\n  same JIRA-keyed shape (`_BASELINE_FIELDS = (\"summary\",\"description\",\"priority\",\"status\",\"assignee\")`,\n  `binding_store.py:46-54`). So feeding `get_baseline(local_id)` where `prev_jira_fields` is read today is\n  shape-for-shape compatible — no field-name translation is required for the swap.\n- **`_INBOUND_MIRRORED_FIELDS` (`{\"title\",...}`, LOCAL names) is a pre-existing partial no-op**, NOT part of this\n  swap. The guard `if field_name in _INBOUND_MIRRORED_FIELDS` (outbound_fields.py:405) never fires for the\n  title/summary field (`\"summary\" ∉ {\"title\",...}`); it only fires for the four coinciding names\n  (description/priority/status/assignee). This asymmetry is UNCHANGED by the swap. Document it; do NOT silently\n  \"fix\" `\"title\"→\"summary\"` as part of the swap (that changes behavior and is out of scope).\n- **`get_baseline` cannot signal \"corrupt\".** It returns `None` for BOTH absent and non-dict baseline\n  (binding_store.py:314-318), and `None` is documented-VALID = \"no ancestor → local-wins\" (ADR 0026 §2). A corrupt\n  `bindings.json` (the baseline lives inside it as `entry[\"baseline\"]`) fails **CLOSED at LOAD**: `BindingStore._load`\n  raises `ValueError` (binding_store.py:103-124) at pass start, before any `get_baseline`. So the fail-closed\n  invariant is preserved by the existing load guard — the consumer swap needs NO new corrupt-detection branch.\n- **`classify()` is NOT wired into the field-differ path for active bindings.** `binding_walk` skips active\n  bindings (`binding_walk.py:169-170` \"handled by the field differ\") and only runs `classify()` on OFF-snapshot\n  pairs. So there is NO production code path where both `classify()`'s decision and the field-differ's action exist\n  for the SAME active binding — comparing them there would require a parallel engine (explicitly forbidden).\n- **`decision_census` is documented-but-never-emitted.** Only `binding_walk_census` is logged\n  (`run_differs.py:652`); `decision_census` appears only in a docstring (`classify.py:351`) with no `.log()` call.\n  So there is no live expand-contract yet — the census task STARTS emitting `decision_census`.\n\n## Remaining CODE\n1. **Add the flag.** New `baseline_consumer_swap: bool = False` in `ReconcilerConfig` (`_config_schema.py` ~355,\n   parsed ~464), alongside — and distinct from — `baseline_dual_write`. Read it ONCE at the orchestration layer\n   (mirror `reconcile.py:936`'s `bool(_load_config().reconciler.baseline_dual_write)`) and thread the bool down,\n   not per-field `_load_config()`. Document the flag + flip procedure in `docs/jira-sync-setup.md`.\n2. **Phase-3 consumer swap (two call-sites, both in `outbound_fields._diff_fields`).**\n   - Site A — direction-suppression: `outbound_fields.py:405-407` (`_local_matches_prev(field_name, local_val,\n     prev_jira_fields or {})`).\n   - Site B — conflict-sink: `outbound_fields.py:519-526` (`_local_matches_prev(fname, local_mapped.get(fname),\n     prev_jira_fields)`).\n   Plumbing: thread `local_id` (already in scope at `outbound_differ.py:622`) into the `_diff_fields` call\n   (`outbound_differ.py:699-708`) plus the `baseline_consumer_swap` bool. `_diff_fields` already receives\n   `binding_store`. When the flag is ON, compute `baseline = binding_store.get_baseline(local_id)` once and pass it\n   (JIRA-keyed, same shape) wherever `prev_jira_fields` is used by the two `_local_matches_prev` calls; when OFF,\n   behavior is byte-for-byte the current `prev_snapshot` path. `None` baseline → the EXISTING absent branch\n   (`_local_matches_prev` returns False → local-wins). Corrupt-store fail-closed is inherited from load time (above);\n   no new consumer branch.\n3. **RED-first direction-preservation property test.** With the flag ON (swapped consumer), assert that for each of\n   the five mirrored fields, when local == baseline the outbound diff SUPPRESSES the field (inbound-wins), and when\n   local != baseline it emits the mutation — matching `direction_is_inbound` (`classify.py:258-273`). RED before the\n   swap wiring, GREEN after. Include the title/summary asymmetry as an explicit documented case (title is not\n   suppressed today — the test pins that unchanged behavior, it is not a regression).\n4. **Census expand-contract.** Emit `decision_census` (the documented-but-missing key) from the same `census(...)`\n   record currently shipped under `binding_walk_census` (`run_differs.py:652`); migrate any consumer to\n   `decision_census`; then DROP `binding_walk_census`. Rollback path for the drop: re-add the `binding_walk_census`\n   emit (one line) — documented in the commit.\n5. **`classifier_legacy_divergence` alert (SCOPED).** Emit it only where BOTH a `classify()` decision and the\n   production action are available for the same binding — i.e. the `binding_walk` (off-snapshot) path. Alert schema:\n   `{classifier_count:int, legacy_count:int, divergent_pairs:list[str] (local_ids), pass_id:str}`. For ACTIVE\n   bindings (field-differ-owned), a per-binding legacy decision is NOT extractable without a parallel engine —\n   DOCUMENT that gap in the alert's docstring; do NOT invent a parallel engine.\n\n## Remaining OPERATIONAL (agent-run with ACLI; guaranteed cleanup) — wall-clock-bound\n- **≥10 CONSECUTIVE clean shadow passes** (`baseline_shadow_check` divergent==0) BEFORE flipping the flag. The\n  streak is DERIVED from sync-log history (query the last N `baseline_shadow_check` events), NOT an in-memory\n  counter, so a fresh GHA process recomputes it; any divergent>0 OR a >20-min gap resets it and emits\n  `baseline_shadow_divergence`. COORDINATION: A3's live remediation pauses the reconciler and RESETS this streak —\n  A3's live pass already ran this session, so the streak starts fresh AFTER it; do not run another A3 pass during\n  the window.\n- **Capped live heal** under bootstrap-strict incl. the GC-after-grace deletion (f8b5-2f30 → REB-530). PRE-HEAL\n  BACKUP covers BOTH sides: export affected Jira issue state (JSON via Jira API) AND tag the tickets branch\n  (`git tag pre-heal-<date>`); if either backup fails, ABORT the heal. Store artifacts in the workflow run\n  artifacts (retention documented).\n- **Flip the flag only after BOTH gates.** Rollback rehearsed: (a) revert the flag to false and confirm the\n  reconciler reverts to `prev_snapshot` arbitration with no divergence, AND (b) force one `--mode dry-run` pass\n  confirming zero mutations; record both workflow run-ids.\n\n## Scope (files EDITED)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_config_schema.py` — add `baseline_consumer_swap`\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` — thread `local_id` + flag into `_diff_fields`\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_fields.py` — `_diff_fields` reads `get_baseline` behind the flag\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/run_differs.py` — census expand-contract; scoped divergence alert\n- `docs/jira-sync-setup.md` — flag + flip/rollback procedure\n- new test file under `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/` — RED-first direction-preservation property test\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] [CODE] `reconciler.baseline_consumer_swap` flag added (distinct from `baseline_dual_write`) + documented in\n      `docs/jira-sync-setup.md`. Proof: `pytest -k baseline_consumer_swap` config-parse test asserts default False +\n      parse.\n- [ ] [CODE] Both `_local_matches_prev` call-sites (outbound_fields.py:405, :519) read `get_baseline(local_id)`\n      behind the flag; flag OFF is byte-for-byte the `prev_snapshot` path; `None` baseline → local-wins; corrupt\n      `bindings.json` still fails closed at load (existing `_load` guard — a test asserts a corrupt store aborts the\n      pass). Proof: named property/unit tests.\n- [ ] [CODE] RED-first direction-preservation property test over the five mapped fields: RED (fails) before the\n      swap wiring, GREEN after; the title/summary asymmetry is pinned as an explicit case.\n- [ ] [CODE] Census emits `decision_census`; consumers migrated; `binding_walk_census` dropped WITH a documented\n      one-line rollback. Proof: a test asserts `decision_census` is emitted and `binding_walk_census` is not.\n- [ ] [CODE] `classifier_legacy_divergence` emitted with the typed schema on the binding_walk (off-snapshot) path;\n      the active-binding non-extractability gap is documented in the alert docstring (no parallel engine).\n- [ ] [OPERATIONAL] ≥10 consecutive clean shadow passes (log-derived streak, reset rule above), not overlapping\n      A3's live pass; evidence (pass_ids / run-ids) recorded on this ticket.\n- [ ] [OPERATIONAL] Capped live heal with a bilateral pre-heal backup (Jira JSON + tickets-branch tag); heal aborts\n      if either backup fails; artifacts stored + linked.\n- [ ] [OPERATIONAL] Flip only after both gates; rollback rehearsed (flag-revert + dry-run run-ids recorded)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783560315585217001,"uuid":"4f68fd5a-cf84-43fd-be17-9fc94716a0ae"}